# Beef on Weck

## The "Lazy" Way

### Ingredients
- 2lbs sliced roast beef from the grocery store
- 1qt Beef Stock / Bone Broth
- 1/2 Tablespoon Minced Garlic
- 1/2 Tablespoon Onion Powder

### Instructions
- If cooking from frozen, ensure roast beef is thawed and all in separate slices (not frozen bunched together)
- Put beef stock, garlic, and onion powder into small crock pot and whisk together
- Throw in the thawed roast beef
- Cook on high for 2 hours, then set to low before serving

